724100f-a.text: Washington Street, west side, south from and including Vesey Street to and including Fulton Street. This is the old Washington Market. About 1925. Ewing Gallery. NO REPRODUCTIONS
724100f-a.folder: Washington Street & Vesey Street, Manhattan, NY

723797f-a.text:
77-81 Vesey Street, at the S.E. corner of Washington Street, showing only the lower stories of building concerned. Shown on the extreme right is a portion of the Washington Market, reputed to be the largest wholesale
vegetable and fruit market in the world.
August 1, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
723797f-a.folder: Vesey Street & Washington Street, Manhattan, NY

723798f-b.text:
(1)
Vesey Street, north side, east from, but not including Washington Street. The view shows the new Post Office in process of construction.
Towering over all is the Woolworth Building.
August 31, 199S.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same; another view.
August 31, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same, at an earlier date, showing clearance;on the site where steel constructhon is in progress on the United States Post Office Building. The building to the right of the Woolworth, is the 44-story Transportation Building at the S.W. corner of Barclay Street and
Broadway.
April 3, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
